We have,<br><br>$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and $$B = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$AB = \left[ {\matrix{
   {1 \times 2 + ( - 1) \times ( - 1)} &amp; {1 \times 3 + ( - 1) \times ( - 2)}  \cr 
   {2 \times 2 + 3 \times ( - 1)} &amp; {2 \times 3 + 3 \times ( - 2)}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   3 &amp; 5  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$BA = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   8 &amp; 7  \cr 
   { - 5} &amp; { - 5}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Clearly, AB $$\ne$$ BA<br><br>Now, AB (A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>) = AB (BA)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> [$$\because$$ (AB)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> = B<sup>$$-$$1</sup> A<sup>$$-$$1</sup>]<br><br>AB (BA)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> is a unit matrix if and only if AB = BA but AB $$\ne$$ BA. So, AB (A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>) is not a unit matrix. Since, AB $$\ne$$ BA, therefore (AB)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> $$\ne$$ A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>.
